        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 4:04PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 404 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles east of Waynesville, or near Canton, moving northeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Canton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
